24. In conducting the risk assessment, a banking corporation shall consider a range of 
factors that are relevant to its activity, including: 
(a) the nature, scale, diversity, and complexity of its business and the services that  
it renders; 
(b) its target markets; 
(c) the number of customers already identified as high-risk; 
(d) the countries or territories to which it is exposed, either directly or via its 
customers’ activity, with emphasis on high risk countries with high levels of 
organized crime or corruption , and/or countries with deficient AML/CFT 
controls as indicated by FATF publications; 
(e) its distribution channels, including the extent of its direct contact with customers 
and its reliance on technology;

